file_content.text: Hate to see you go. I felt pretty invincible with you around.
They say the dark side isn't more powerful--but every time a Jedi dies, I'm not so sure.
Corellia used to be a great place to visit. Blasted Empire. No respect for vacation spots.
Let's drive these cantina-bombing scum off Corellia for good.
You suppose the Corellians keep some cantinas underground? No reason I'd ask.
Stupid Empire and its Mandalorian mercenaries! Those flying bucket-heads shot every bottle in the cantina!
I've been running and fighting for days. All I wanted was a drink, but that's obviously too much to ask!
It's Corellia. I'm sure there's another cantina somewhere.
Calm down.
You'd think that, but the Empire is determined to deny us refreshment. Believe me, I've looked!
You're one of the only Jedi left on Corellia. Who are you?
What's your name?
Nae Nuuv, former Padawan to Master Kaedan.
I finished my trials right before coming to this star-forsaken planet. I've been fighting for my life ever since.
Shut up and listen.
The Jedi Council appointed me supreme commander here. Jedi reinforcements are gathering at these coordinates. On your way.
Hope those reinforcements brought something decent to drink.
Yeah, me too. Can't fight with a dry mouth.
At least he's focused on something....
He's an excellent candidate for shock troop duty.
Watch this one closely, Master Jedi. He's showing signs of combat stress.
Jedi transports = austere // Probability of additional beverages = low
Our last supreme commander got vaporized. I hope you're luckier than her....
You're welcome to join us. We need all the help we can get.
This is for burning down my favorite cantina!
Run while you can, yellow-eyed Sith scum!
You have debts--and we're here to collect!
Feel the Force!
Did you like that? There's more where it came from!
Jedi don't get angry--but I'll make an exception for you filth!
Not so tough against a Jedi strike team, are you?
I shouldn't say this, but I'm actually having fun!
